description: Line 1 Yonge-University has 38 stations, and is a “U-shaped” route running generally in a south and then north direction. The route operates from the northern area of Yonge Street and Finch Avenue East, south to Union Station in downtown Toronto, and then north again to the area of Highway 7 and Jane Street. Line 1 connects with Line 2 at Bloor-Yonge, St George and Spadina stations, and it connects with Line 4 at Sheppard-Yonge Station.

description: Line 2 Bloor-Danforth has 31 stations, running generally in an east-west direction along Bloor Street West, Bloor Street East and Danforth Avenue. The route operates from the western area of Dundas Street West and Kipling Avenue, east to the area of Bloor Street and Yonge Street in downtown Toronto, and continues east to the area of Eglinton Avenue East and Kennedy Road. Line 1 connects with Line 2 at Bloor-Yonge, St George and Spadina stations.

description: Line 4 Sheppard has five stations, running in an east-west direction along Sheppard Avenue East. The route operates from the area of Yonge Street and Sheppard Avenue, east to the area of Sheppard Avenue East and Don Mills Road. Line 4 connects with Line 1 at Sheppard-Yonge Station.

Accessible service is provided on the route. Bathurst Station is an accessible subway station. Bike racks are available on this route.

One single service is operated. The 7 (Bathurst Station-Steeles) branch operates all day, every day.

The route is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

The request stop program is available to all customers travelling along by bus between 9:00 PM and 5:00AM. Request Stop allows any customer who is feeling vulnerable to get off the bus between regular TTC stops.

The 24 Victoria Park bus route operates between Victoria Park Station on Line 2 Bloor-Danforth, the area of Victoria Park Avenue and Steeles Avenue East, and Don Mills Station on Line 4 Sheppard, generally in a north-south direction. Accessible service is provided on the route. Both Victoria Park and Don Mills Stations are accessible subway stations. Bike racks are available on this route.

Two services are operated. The 24A (Victoria Park Station-Steeles) branch operates all day, every day. The 24B (Victoria Park Station-Don Mills Station via Consumers Rd) short-turn branch operates during the daytime, from Monday to Friday only (service in the Consumers Road area at other times of the week is provided by the 167 Pharmacy North route).

The 24A (Victoria Park Station-Steeles) branch is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

Southbound 24A to Victoria Park Station

These buses operate from the Victoria Park/Steeles off-street loop via south on Victoria Park Avenue and east on Denton Avenue to Victoria Park Station.

Northbound 24A to Steeles

These buses operate from Victoria Park Station via north on Victoria Park Avenue to the Victoria Park/Steeles off-street loop (on the east side of Victoria Park Avenue, north of Steeles Avenue East).

Southbound 24B to Victoria Park Station via Consumers Road

These buses operate from Don Mills Station via east on Sheppard Avenue East, south on Consumers Road, west, south and east on Yorkland Boulevard, east on Consumers Road, south on Victoria Park Avenue, and east on Denton Avenue to Victoria Park Station.

Northbound 24B to Don Mills Station via Consumers Road

These buses operate from Victoria Park Station via north on Victoria Park Avenue, west on Consumers Road, west, north and east on Yorkland Boulevard, north on Consumers Road, and west on Sheppard Avenue East to Don Mills Station.

All buses on the route serve local bus stops along the route.

The request stop program is available to all customers travelling along by bus between 9:00 PM and 5:00AM. Request Stop allows any customer who is feeling vulnerable to get off the bus between regular TTC stops.

description:
The 25 Don Mills bus route operates between Pape Station on Line 2 Bloor-Danforth, Don Mills Station on Line 4 Sheppard, and the area of Don Mills Road and Steeles Avenue East, generally in a north-south direction. Accessible service is provided on the route. Both Don Mills Station and Pape Station are accessible subway stations. Bike racks are available on this route.
 
Three services are operated. The 25A (Pape Station-Steeles via Don Mills Station) operates during the evenings, from Monday to Friday, and at all times on Saturday, Sunday, and holidays. The 25B (Pape Station- Don Mills Station) and 25C (Don Mills Station-Steeles) operate during the daytime from Monday to Friday.

Southbound 25B to Pape Station

These buses operate from Don Mills Station, south on Don Mills Road, west on Overlea Boulevard, south on Millwood Road, south on Leaside Bridge, and south on Pape Avenue to Pape Station.

Northbound 25C to Steeles

These buses operate from Don Mills Station, north on Don Mills Road, east on Steeles Avenue East, south on Townsend Road, and west on Freshmeadow Drive to Don Mills Road.

Southbound 25C to Don Mills Station

These buses operate from Freshmeadow Drive and Don Mills Road via south on Don Mills Road to Don Mills Station.

message: Please note: Effective October 12, 2025, the TTC’s routes and schedules pages, as well as most trip planning apps, will not display route diversions for the 29 Dufferin, 304 King, 329 Dufferin Night Bus, 503 Kingston Rd, 504 King, 508 Lake Shore and 929 Dufferin Express routes. However, construction at King Street West and Dufferin Street will continue until mid-November 2025. The Transit app may show partial detours, but travel times may not be accurate. Please call the Customer Information team at 416-393-4636 for assistance.

description:
The 29 Dufferin bus route operates between Wilson Station on Line 1 Yonge-University and Exhibition Place, generally in a north-south direction. It also serves Dufferin Station on Line 2 Bloor-Danforth. Accessible service is provided on the route. Both Wilson Station and Dufferin Station are accessible subway stations. Bike racks are available on this route.

Two services are operated. The 29A (Wilson Station-Exhibition/Dufferin Gate) branch operates during the midday and evening from Monday to Friday, and during the evening on Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays during the Fall and Winter. During the Spring and Summer, this branch operates all day, every day. The 29C (Wilson Station-Exhibition/Princes’ Gate) branch operates during the peak periods from Monday to Friday, and during the daytime on Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays during the Fall and Winter.

Service between Wilson Station and Exhibition (Dufferin Gate) is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

Southbound 29A to Exhibition (Dufferin Gate)

These buses operate from Wilson Station via west on Wilson Avenue, south on Dufferin Street, west on Springhurst Avenue, and south on Fort Rouille Street to Dufferin Gate Loop.

Northbound 29A to Wilson Station

These buses operate from Dufferin Gate Loop via north on Dufferin Street and east on Wilson Avenue to Wilson Station.

Southbound 29C to Exhibition (Princes’ Gates)

These buses operate from Wilson Station via west on Wilson Avenue, south on Dufferin Street, east on Saskatchewan Road, east on Manitoba Drive, and south on Canada Boulevard to Princes’ Gate Loop (the cul-de-sac northwest of Princes’ Gate).

Northbound 29C to Wilson Station

These buses operate from Princes’ Gate Loop via south on Canada Boulevard, west on Princes’ Boulevard, north and west on Nunavut Road, north on Nova Scotia Avenue, west on Manitoba Drive, west on Saskatchewan Road, north on Dufferin Street, west on Springhurst Avenue, south on Fort Rouille Street, east through Dufferin Gate Loop, north on Dufferin Street, and east on Wilson Avenue to Wilson Station.

All buses on the route serve local bus stops along the route.

The request stop program is available to all customers travelling along by bus between 9:00 PM and 5:00AM. Request Stop allows any customer who is feeling vulnerable to get off the bus between regular TTC stops.

The 30 High Park bus route operates between High Park Station on Line 2 Bloor-Danforth and Runnymede and Dundas, generally in a north-south direction. Accessible service is provided on the route. High Park Station is not an accessible subway Station. Bike racks are available on this route.

All buses on the route serve local bus stops along the route
The request stop program is available to all customers travelling along by bus between 9:00 PM and 5:00AM. Request Stop allows any customer who is feeling vulnerable to get off the bus between regular TTC stops.

description:
The 32 Eglinton West bus route operates between Eglinton Station on Line 1 Yonge-University and the area of Eglinton Avenue West and Renforth Drive, generally in an east-west direction. It also serves Eglinton West Station on Line 1 Yonge-University. Accessible service is provided on the route. Both Eglinton and Eglinton West Stations are accessible subway stations. Bike racks are available on this route.

Three services are operated. The 32A (Eglinton Station-Renforth Station), 32C (Eglinton Station-Jane & Lawrence via Trethewey) and 32D (Eglinton West Station-Jane & Emmett) branches operate all day, every day. 

The Eglinton Station to Skymark and Renforth portion of the route is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

These buses operate from Eglinton Station via north on Duplex Avenue, west on Eglinton Avenue West, through Eglinton West Station, continuing west on Eglinton Avenue West, to Renforth Station.

Eastbound 32A to Eglinton Station

These buses operate from Renforth Station via east on Eglinton Avenue West, through Eglinton West Station, continuing east on Eglinton Avenue West, and south on Duplex Avenue to Eglinton Station.

Eastbound 32C to Eglinton Station

These buses operate from Pine Street and Lawrence Avenue West via east on Lawrence Avenue West, south on Jane Street, east and south on Trethewey Drive, east on Eglinton Avenue West, through Eglinton West Station, continuing east on Eglinton Avenue West, and south on Duplex Avenue to Eglinton Station.

Westbound 32D to Jane & Emmett

These buses operate from Eglinton West Station via west on Eglinton Avenue West, and north and west on Emmett Avenue to Verona Avenue.

Eastbound 32D to Eglinton West Station

These buses operate from Verona Avenue via east on Emmett Avenue, south on Jane Street, and east on Eglinton Avenue West to Eglinton West Station.

All buses on the route serve local bus stops along the route.

The request stop program is available to all customers travelling along by bus between 9:00 PM and 5:00AM. Request Stop allows any customer who is feeling vulnerable to get off the bus between regular TTC stops.

description:
The 35 Jane bus route operates between Jane Station on Line 2 Bloor-Danforth and Pioneer Village Station on Line 1 Yonge-University, generally in a north-south direction.  Accessible service is provided on this route as Jane Station and Pioneer Village Station are accessible subway stations.

Two services are operated. The 35A (Jane Station-Pioneer Village Station) operates all day, every day. The 35B (Jane Station-Pioneer Village Station via Hullmar) operates during peak periods, from Monday to Friday only.

Service between Jane Station and Steeles Ave W is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

Southbound 35A: from Pioneer Village Station, regular route to Jane St at Weatherell St, continue southbound Jane St, eastbound to Jane Station Bus Bay #5.

Northbound 35A from Jane Station Bus Bay #5, continue westbound to Armadale Ave, southbound Armadale Ave, westbound Bloor St W, northbound Jane St, continue regular route to Pioneer Village Station.

Southbound 35B: from Pioneer Village Station, regular route to Jane St at Weatherell St, continue southbound Jane St, eastbound to Jane Station Bus Bay #5.

Northbound 35B from Jane Station Bus Bay #5, continue westbound to Armadale Ave, southbound Armadale Ave, westbound Bloor St W, northbound Jane St, continue regular route to Pioneer Village Station. 

Service is provided at all local stops along the route.

The Request Stop program is available to all customers travelling alone by bus between 9:00 p.m. and 5:00 a.m. Request Stop allows any customer who is feeling vulnerable to get off the bus between regular TTC stops.

description:
The 36 Finch West bus route operates between Finch Station on Line 1 Yonge-University and the Humberwood Boulevard area, generally in an east-west direction. It also serves Finch West Station on Line 1 Yonge-University. Accessible service is provided on the route. Finch Station and Finch West Station are both accessible subway stations. Bike racks are available on this route.

Three services are generally operated. Service is provided between Finch Station and Finch West Station at all times, operates at all times, seven days a week. Service is provided between Finch West Station and the Humberwood Boulevard area at all times, seven days a week. At most times of the week buses do not operate through Finch West Station, and a change of buses is required. Additional short-turn service is operated during the peak periods between Finch West Station and the Milvan Drive area.

Service between Finch Station and the Humberwood Boulevard area is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

Westbound 36 to Humberwood

These buses operate from Finch Station via west on Finch Avenue West, north on Tangiers Road, west on Four Winds Drive to Finch West Station. From Finch West Station via west on Four Winds Drive, south on Keele Street, west on Finch Avenue West, south on Humber College Boulevard, west on Humberline Drive, and south and west on Humberwood Boulevard to Humberwood Loop.

These buses operate from Humberwood Loop via north and east on Humberwood Boulevard, east on Humberline Drive, north on Humber College Boulevard, east on Finch Avenue West, north on Keele Road, east on Four Winds Drive to Finch West Station. From Finch West Station via east on Four Winds Drive, south on Tangiers Road, and east on Finch Avenue West to Finch Station.

Westbound 36A to Finch West Station

These buses operate from Finch Station via west on Finch Avenue West, north on Tangiers Road, west on Four Winds Drive to Finch West Station.

Eastbound 36 to Finch Station

These buses operate from Finch West Station via east on Four Winds Drive, south on Tangiers Road, and east on Finch Avenue West to Finch Station.

Westbound 36A to Humberwood

These buses operate from Finch West Station via west on Four Winds Drive, south on Keele Street, west on Finch Avenue West, south on Humber College Boulevard, west on Humberline Drive, and south and west on Humberwood Boulevard to Humberwood Loop.

Eastbound 36A to Finch West Station

These buses operate from Humberwood Loop via north and east on Humberwood Boulevard, east on Humberline Drive, north on Humber College Boulevard, east on Finch Avenue West, north on Keele Road, east on Four Winds Drive to Finch West Station.

Westbound 36D to Weston Road and Milvan

These buses operate from Finch West Station via west on Four Winds Drive, south on Keele Street, west on Finch Avenue West, north on Weston Road, northwest on Toryork Drive, and south and east on Milvan Drive to Penn Drive.

Eastbound 36D to Finch West Station

These buses operate from Milvan Drive and Penn Drive via south on Milvan Drive, east on Finch Avenue West, north on Keele Road, east on Four Winds Drive to Finch West Station.

Westbound 36F to Weston Road and Milvan via Fenmar

These buses operate from Finch West Station via west on Four Winds Drive, south on Keele Street, west on Finch Avenue West, north on Weston Road, northwest on Fenmar Drive, southwest on Ormont Drive, northwest on Toryork Drive, and south and east on Milvan Drive to Penn Drive.

Eastbound 38B to U OF T Scarborough

These buses operate from Scarborough Centre Station via east on Triton Road, south on McCowan Road, east on Ellesmere Road, southeast on Military Trail to the University of Toronto at Scarborough.

Westbound 38 to Scarborough Centre

description:
The 85 Sheppard East bus route operates between Sheppard-Yonge Station on the Yonge-University-Spadina Subway, Don Mills Station on the Sheppard Subway, and Rouge Hill GO Station, generally in an east-west direction.  It also operates to the Toronto Zoo on weekends and holidays only.  Accessible service is provided on the route.  Both Sheppard-Yonge and Don Mills Stations are accessible subway stations. Bike racks are available on this route.

Two basic services are operated, with some additional variations. Service is provided between Sheppard-Yonge Station and Don Mills Station at all times, seven days a week. Service is provided between Don Mills Station and Rouge Hill GO Station at all times, seven days a week. At most times of the week buses do not operate through Don Mills Station, and a change of buses is required. Additional short-turn service is provided at busy times between Don Mills Station and Meadowvale. During the daytime on Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays, service is provided from Don Mills Station to the Toronto Zoo and from Rouge Hill GO Station to the Toronto Zoo. During the summer, this Toronto Zoo service is also operated in the early evening on Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays.

85 Sheppard East

Service between Don Mills Station and Meadowvale Road is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day. 

Eastbound 85 TO MEADOWVALE

These buses operate from Sheppard-Yonge Station via east on Sheppard Avenue East, north on Don Mills Road, through Don Mills Station, continuing east on Sheppard Avenue East, and north on Meadowvale Road to Meadowvale Loop (on the east side of Meadowvale Road, north of Sheppard Avenue East).

Westbound 85 TO SHEPPARD-YONGE STN

These buses operate from Meadowvale Loop via south on Meadowvale Road, west on Sheppard Avenue East, through Don Mills Station, continuing south on Don Mills Road, and west on Sheppard Avenue East to Sheppard-Yonge Station.

Eastbound 85A TO DON MILLS STN

These shuttle buses operate from Sheppard-Yonge Station via east on Sheppard Avenue East, and north on Don Mills Road to Don Mills Station.

Westbound 85A TO SHEPPARD-YONGE STN

These shuttle buses operate from Don Mills Station via south on Don Mills Road, and west on Sheppard Avenue East to Sheppard-Yonge Station.

Eastbound 85A TO ROUGE HILL GO STN

These buses operate from Don Mills Station via east and southeast on Sheppard Avenue East, south on Port Union Road, east on Island Road, and south on East Avenue to Rouge Hill GO Station.

Westbound 85A TO DON MILLS STN

These buses operate from Rouge Hill GO Station via north on East Avenue, west on Island Road, north on Port Union Road, and northwest and west on Sheppard Avenue East to Don Mills Station.

Eastbound 85A TO ROUGE HILL GO STN VIA TORONTO ZOO

These buses operate from Don Mills Station via east on Sheppard Avenue East, and north on Meadowvale Road to Toronto Zoo Loop, continuing south on Meadowvale Road, east and southeast on Sheppard Avenue East, south on Port Union Road, east on Island Road, and south on East Avenue to Rouge Hill GO Station.

Westbound 85A TO DON MILLS STN VIA TORONTO ZOO

These buses operate from Rouge Hill GO Station via north on East Avenue, west on Island Road, north on Port Union Road, northwest and west on Sheppard Avenue East, north on Meadowvale Road to Toronto Zoo Loop, continuing south on Meadowvale Road, and west on Sheppard Avenue East to Don Mills Station.

Eastbound 85B TO TORONTO ZOO

These buses operate from Don Mills Station via east on Sheppard Avenue East, and north on Meadowvale Road to Toronto Zoo Loop.

Westbound 85B TO DON MILLS STN

These buses operate from Toronto Zoo Loop via south on Meadowvale Road, and west on Sheppard Avenue East to Don Mills Station.

All buses on the route serve local bus stops along the route.

Four services are operated. The 191A (Kipling Stn-Humber College) short-turn branch operates a limited peak period service from Monday to Friday only. The 191B (Kipling Stn-Steeles) branch operates at most times, seven days a week. The 191C (Kipling Stn-Humber College via Attwell) branch operates during the peak periods from Monday to Friday only. The 191D (Kipling Stn-Steeles via Royalcrest) branch operates during the peak periods from Monday to Friday only.

Service between Kipling Station and Steeles Avenue is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

description:
A seasonal route operating between Rouge Hill GO Station and Toronto Zoo via Port Union Road and Sheppard Avenue East from May to October. 

This service will operate Saturdays and Sundays, from 8 a.m. to 9 p.m.

In the month of May, weekday service operates Monday to Friday from 6:30 p.m. to 8 p.m. Starting in June, weekday service operates Monday to Friday from 8 a.m. to 9 p.m. Holiday service will operate on Labour Day and weekend service will continue until October.

Buses arrive every 20 minutes.

Northbound:

from Rouge Hill GO Station, west on Lawrence Avenue East, north on Port Union Road, north on Sheppard Avenue East and north on Meadowvale Road, to Toronto Zoo.

Southbound:

from Toronto Zoo, south on Meadowvale Road, south on Sheppard Avenue East, south on Port Union Road and east on Lawrence Avenue East, to Rouge Hill GO Station.

Please note: Effective October 12, 2025, TTC’s routes and schedules pages and most trip planning apps will show route diversions for 301/501 Queen streetcars and 503 Kingston Rd replacement buses in preparation for the start of construction on Queen Street East between Broadview Avenue and Davies Avenues in late October. Service on the 303 Kingston Rd is currently suspended. Customers travelling overnight between approximately 1:30 a.m. until the start of subway service from Queen Street East to Kingston Road will need to take a 301 Queen streetcar and then transfer to the 322 Coxwell bus at Queen Street East at Kingston Road to continue along Kingston Road to Bingham Loop (Victoria Park.)

Please note: These route diversions may be modified on a temporary basis to accommodate additional construction activities planned across the streetcar network. Please check route schedules and trip planning apps for the latest service information.

The 501 Queen streetcar route operates between Neville Park Loop and Long Branch Loop, generally in an east-west direction. It serves Queen and Osgoode Stations on Line 1 Yonge-University. Both Queen and Osgoode Stations are accessible subway stations.

The route is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

During the daytime and early evening, seven days a week, one service is operated:

During the late evening, a single service operates: 501 (Long Branch-Neville Park).

Eastbound 501: from Humber Loop via east on The Queensway, east on Queen Street West, south on York Street, east on Adelaide Street West, east on Adelaide Street East, north on Church Street, and east on Queen Street East to Neville Park Loop. Westbound 501: from Neville Park Loop via west on Queen Street East, south on Church Street, west on Richmond Street East, west on Richmond Street West, north on York Street, west on Queen Street West, and west on The Queensway to Humber Loop.

After 10:00 p.m.

message:
Please note: Effective October 12, 2025, the TTC’s routes and schedules pages, as well as most trip planning apps, will not display route diversions for the 29 Dufferin, 304 King, 329 Dufferin Night Bus, 503 Kingston Rd, 504 King, 508 Lake Shore and 929 Dufferin Express routes. However, construction at King Street West and Dufferin Street will continue until mid-November 2025. The Transit app may show partial detours, but travel times may not be accurate. Please call the Customer Information team at 416-393-4636 for assistance.

503 Kingston Rd streetcar service will be replaced by buses. The buses will operate between Dufferin Street and Bingham Loop.

Service on the 303 Kingston Rd is currently suspended. Customers travelling overnight between approximately 1:30 a.m. until the start of subway service from Queen Street East to Kingston Road will need to take a 301 Queen streetcar and then transfer to the 322 Coxwell bus at Queen Street East at Kingston Road to continue along Kingston Road to Bingham Loop (Victoria Park.)

Please note: These route diversions may be modified on a temporary basis to accommodate additional construction activities planned across the streetcar network. Please check route schedules and trip planning apps for the latest service information.

description:
The 508 Lake Shore streetcar route operates between Long Branch Loop and the area of King Street East and Parliament Street, generally in an east-west direction. It also serves the St. Andrew and King Stations on Line 1 Yonge-University. Service is operated with low-floor, accessible streetcars.

Two services are operated.  The 508 (Long Branch-Parliament) morning branch operates five Eastbound only trips during the morning peak period, from Monday to Friday only.  The 508 (Parliament-Long Branch) afternoon branch operates five Westbound only trips during the afternoon peak period, from Monday to Friday only.

AM peak period

 

Eastbound 508 (Long Branch-Broadview Stn): From Long Branch Loop via east on Lake Shore Boulevard West, through Humber Loop, east on The Queensway, east on King Street West, east on King Street East, east on Queen Street East, and north on Broadview Avenue to Broadview Station.

 

Westbound (Morning Peak Period): Streetcars return to Roncesvalles yard via west on Erindale Avenue, south on Broadview Avenue, west on Queen Street East, west on King Street East, west on King Street West and west on The Queensway to Roncesvalles Carhouse.

 

PM peak period

 

Eastbound 508 (Roncesvalles yard-Broadview Stn) From Roncesvalles yard via south on Roncesvalles Avenue, east on King Street West, east on King Street East, east on Queen Street East, and north on Broadview Avenue to Broadview Station.

 

Westbound 508 (Broadview Stn-Long Branch): From Broadview Station via west on Erindale Avenue, south on Broadview Avenue, west on Queen Street East, west on King Street East, west on King Street West, west on The Queensway, through Humber Loop, and west on Lake Shore Boulevard West to Long Branch Loop.

 

All streetcars on the route serve local streetcar stops along the route.

Accessible service is provided with low-floor streetcars. Spadina Station (Line 2 Bloor-Danforth platforms only) and Union Station are accessible subway stations. Interior bike racks are available on this route.

Three services are operated. The 510A (Spadina Station-Union Station) branch operates at all times. The 510B (Spadina Station-Queens Quay/Spadina) and 510C (Spadina Station-King) branches provide additional service at various times of the week.

The route is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day. Proof-of-payment is required at all times.

description:
The 900 Airport Express bus route operates between Kipling Station on the Bloor-Danforth Subway and Toronto Pearson International Airport, generally in a north-south direction.  Accessible service is provided on the route.  Kipling Station is an accessible subway station. Bike racks are available on this route. Luggage racks are available on this route.

One single service is operated:  the 900 (Kipling Stn-Pearson Airport) branch operates all day everyday.

The route is part of the 10 Minute Network, and operates 10 minutes or better, all day, every day.

Northbound 900 Airport Express to Pearson Airport

These buses operate from Kipling Station via west on St. Albans Road, north on Aukland Road, west on Dundas Street West, north on Highway 427, west on Dixon Road, and west on Airport Road to Toronto Pearson International Airport, (stopping first on Jetliner Road at Airport Road (Ground Level), then at Terminal 1 (Ground Level), and then at Terminal 3 (Arrivals Level). Northbound 900 buses operate EXPRESS from Kipling Station to Pearson Airport, stopping only at Dundas Street West and East Mall Crescent.

Southbound 900 Express to Kipling Station

These buses operate from Pearson Airport Terminal 3 via south on Highway 427, east on Dundas Street West, and south on Aukland Road to Kipling Station.  Southbound 900 buses operate EXPRESS from Pearson Airport Terminal 3 to Kipling Station, stopping only at Dundas Street West and East Mall Crescent, and at Kipling Station.

The 900 Airport Express buses do not serve local bus stops along the route.

description:

However, construction at King Street West and Dufferin Street will continue until mid-November 2025. The Transit app may show partial detours, but travel times may not be accurate. Please call the Customer Information team at 416-393-4636 for assistance.
